Female (from Thirumangalam): Prosoma straw colored, appearing transparent (
Figs. 1
E–H); eyes on white tubercles, except PME that are very small, largely separated from the lateral ones (
Fig. 3A
); venter smooth, sternum almost round (
Fig. 3B
); chelicerae conical shaped with very large, prominent dorsal hump, cheliceral promargin with one apical tooth (
Fig. 3C
); dorsum of tibiae, metatarsi and tarsi of the first three legs irregularly covered with short bristles, spination as in male, legs III and IV without spines, metatarsus of leg IV with conspicuous hair tuft; opisthosoma less hairy than in male, not smooth, with comma-shaped black patches posteriolaterally; median spinnerets covered with some black spots. 
Epigyne
(
Figs. 3D,E
): epigynal groove with anteriorly elongated, sclerotized epigynal sutures, spermathecae globular, SPO on distinct stalks, FD elongated, CD very short, indistinct.
